vulnerability.name: USN-7543-1
vulnerability.description: Jan Różański discovered that libsoup incorrectly handled certain headers when sending HTTP/2 requests over TLS. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service. This issue only affected libsoup3 in Ubuntu 24.04 LTS, Ubuntu 24.10, and Ubuntu 25.04. (CVE-2025-32908)  Jan Różański discovered that libsoup incorrectly parsed certain response headers. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service. (CVE-2025-4476)

statements.status_notes: libsoup could be made to crash if it received specially crafted network traffic.
